<TITLE> Mob kills three suspected hijackers in Keraniganj </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 8 (bdnews24.com)A mob beat three persons to death on Thursday night suspecting them to be auto-rickshaw hijackers in south Keraniganj, police said. The dead were identified as 'Akter', 45, Shah Alam, 40 and 'Selim', 48. Another seriously injured, 'Akash', 27, was admitted to Dhaka Medical College Hospital under police custody. Nilotpal Dey, South Keraniganj police chief, said at 9pm Akter, Shah Alam, Selim and Akash rented an auto-rickshaw at Kadamtali intersection to go to Mirzapore. On the way at a desolate spot in Standbazaar, the four alleged hijackers twirled a gamchha , hand-made towel, around the neck of the driver, 'Faruque', and threatened to kill him wielding a machete. Faruque screamed and villagers from the neighbourhoods rushed to the spot and started beating them up. Police arrived to the rescue of the four, sent them to Dhaka Medical College Hospital, where three died. Arif, the owner of the three-wheeler, filed a robbery case at the police station against Akash. bdnews2
